  "prompt": "What are some examples of petrochemical products?",
  "response": "Petrochemical products are derived from petroleum or natural gas and are used in a variety of applications. Here are some common examples:\n\n1. **Plastics:**\n   - Polyethylene (PE)\n   - Polypropylene (PP)\n   - Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC)\n   - Polystyrene (PS)\n   - Polyethylene Terephthalate (PET)\n\n2. **Synthetic Fibers:**\n   - Nylon\n   - Polyester\n   - Acrylic\n\n3. **Rubber:**\n   - Styrene-Butadiene Rubber (SBR)\n   - Polybutadiene Rubber\n   - Ethylene Propylene Diene Monomer (EPDM)\n\n4. **Fertilizers:**\n   - Ammonia\n   - Urea\n\n5. **Industrial Chemicals:**\n   - Methanol\n   - Ethylene Glycol\n   - Propylene Glycol\n\n6. **Solvents:**\n   - Toluene\n   - Benzene\n   - Xylene\n\n7. **Detergents and Surfactants:**\n   - Linear Alkylbenzene Sulfonates (LABS)\n   - Nonylphenol Ethoxylates\n\n8. **Adhesives and Coatings:**\n   - Epoxy Resins\n   - Polyurethane\n\n9. **Cosmetics:**\n   - Paraffin Wax\n   - Certain types of silicones\n\n10. **Pharmaceuticals:**\n    - Various intermediates and active ingredients used in drug manufacturing.\n\nThese products serve diverse industries, including packaging, textiles, automotive, construction, and consumer goods.",
